  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>Romano pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into large pieces </p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into wedges</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>tomato</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle with <strong>olive oil </strong>and put in the oven for 20 min or until softened </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-pepper-linguine-with-tenderstem/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Cook the <strong>linguine</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once done, drain the linguine, reserving 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>\n<p>Return the <strong>linguine</strong> to the pot<strong> </strong>and keep warm </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-pepper-linguine-with-tenderstem/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel the <strong>garlic</strong> </p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>Tenderstem</strong> <strong>broccoli</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> to the baking tray, drizzle with<strong> olive oil</strong> and return the tray to the oven for 10-15 min or until softened </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-pepper-linguine-with-tenderstem/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1] </span><strong>vegetable stock cube</strong> in the reserved <strong>pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-pepper-linguine-with-tenderstem/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the broccoli is almost done, remove the <strong>tomato</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> and transfer straight to a <strong>food processor</strong></p>\n<p>Leave the <strong>Tenderstem</strong> <strong>broccoli</strong> on the tray </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>flaked</strong> <strong>almonds</strong> to the baking tray and return the tray to the oven for 5 min further</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-pepper-linguine-with-tenderstem/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> hazelnuts, red wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>to a <strong>food processor </strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>romesco sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-pepper-linguine-with-tenderstem/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> romesco sauce</strong> to the <strong>linguine</strong> and give everything a good old mix up </p>\n<p>Tip: if cooled, reheat the romesco linguine over a medium heat with a splash of water for 1 min</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-pepper-linguine-with-tenderstem/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Garnish the <strong>romesco linguine</strong> with the<strong> Tenderstem broccoli</strong> and <strong>flaked almonds</strong> </p>\n<p>Drizzle with<strong> olive oil </strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
